> what's like the best automation rate in your opinion:

    - so basically, there is no fixed best automation rate, because it depends
      on the project, application stability and requirements

    - from my experience, a good practical range is around 60 t0 80 percent
      automation, mainly covering stable and high-priority scenarios.

    - we should focus on automating regression and critical workflows, because
      they provide the maximum value

    - at the same time, trying to automate 100 percent is not always efficient,
      because it increases maintenance effort, especially for frequently changing features

    - so in my opinion, the best automation rete is not about the number, but
      about achieving that right balance between automation and manual testing
